templateAssets.content: Thank you for your interest in CSU Dominguez Hills! This articulation agreement displays lower-division course requirements specific to the major. Students are advised to seek advisement from a counselor when planning to transfer to CSU Dominguez Hills and refer to the University Catalog to learn more about this major and its features. Detailed admissions requirements for transfer students are available on the CSUDH campus website. Statutory Requirements/American Institutions(AI): Completion of American Institutions (U.S. Constitution, U.S. American History, and California State and local government) is a baccalaureate degree requirement for the California State University system. This requirement may be met prior to transfer with eligible California Community College (CCC) courses designated as US-1, US-2, and US-3 (see your community college's Transferability List for CSU AI courses). Completion of American Institutions prior to transfer is most advantageous and strongly encouraged, as a number of CCC AI courses may also double-count for General Education.
